    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The view "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "dbo.uvw_FindColumnDefinitionPlusDefaultAndCheckConstraint",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to provide detailed metadata about columns in the database, including their data types, default constraints, and check constraints. The view aims to consolidate information from various system views and tables, such as "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "sys.all_columns",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "sys.tables",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "INFORMATION_SCHEMA.CHECK_CONSTRAINTS",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". However, the current implementation is commented out, leaving only a placeholder column in the view definition. This suggests that the view was intended for development or debugging purposes but was not finalized due to errors in the database project."
        }
      ]
